---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { getDictionary } from "../../i18n";

const lang = "en";
const t = getDictionary(lang);
---

<BaseLayout
  lang={lang}
  title={`${t.nav.privacy} | ${t.company.nameEn}`}
  description={t.nav.privacy}
>
  <h1>{t.nav.privacy}</h1>

<p>
This Privacy Policy describes how ILOHA OpenLab LLC ("Company", "we", "us", or "our")
collects and processes personal data in accordance with the
EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).
</p>

<h2>1. Data Controller</h2>
<p>
ILOHA OpenLab LLC<br/>
Japan<br/>
Email: contact@iloha-openlab.com
</p>

<h2>2. Personal Data We Collect</h2>
<p>
We collect personal data only when voluntarily provided by you, such as:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Name</li>
  <li>Email address</li>
  <li>Information contained in email communications</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Purpose of Processing</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Responding to inquiries</li>
  <li>Providing requested information</li>
  <li>Business communication</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. Legal Basis for Processing (Article 6 GDPR)</h2>
<p>Processing is based on:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Your consent (Article 6(1)(a))</li>
  <li>Our legitimate interest in conducting business communications (Article 6(1)(f))</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
<p>
Personal data is retained only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes
for which it was collected or to comply with legal obligations.
</p>

<h2>6. International Data Transfers</h2>
<p>
Personal data may be processed in Japan.
The European Commission has recognized Japan as providing an adequate level of data protection.
</p>

<h2>7. Your Rights Under GDPR</h2>
<p>You have the right to:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Access your personal data</li>
  <li>Request rectification</li>
  <li>Request erasure</li>
  <li>Restrict processing</li>
  <li>Data portability</li>
  <li>Object to processing</li>
  <li>Withdraw consent at any time</li>
</ul>

<p>
To exercise your rights, contact us at:
contact@iloha-openlab.com
</p>

<h2>8. Cookies</h2>
<p>
We use only essential cookies necessary for website functionality.
Analytics or tracking cookies are used only after obtaining user consent.
</p>

<h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
<p>
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.
The updated version will be posted on this page.
</p>
  <nav style="margin-top: 2rem;">
    <a href="/en/">{t.nav.home}</a> |
    <a href="/en/news/">{t.nav.news}</a> |
    <a href="/en/logo-policy/">{t.nav.logoPolicy}</a> |
    <a href="/ja/privacy/">日本語</a>
  </nav>
</BaseLayout>